# Development Workflow

This project follows an AI-assisted development workflow powered by [claude-workflow](https://github.com/{{WORKFLOW_REPO}}).

## Lifecycle Overview

```
IDEA â†’ [/draft] â†’ BACKLOG â†’ [/plan] â†’ READY â†’ [/implement] â†’ [/verify] â†’ merge (local) â†’ DONE
                                                                                            â†“
                                                                                   [/release] â†’ RELEASED
```
Or run the whole chain with **`/ship`** (from a spec list or a topic).

## Commands

| Command | Phase | What it does |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| `/draft feature\|bug "title"` | Draft | Create a raw backlog entry (no planning) |
| `/plan FEAT-001` | Planning | One light pass: goal, observable acceptance criteria, subtasks |
| `/implement FEAT-001` | Implementation | Per subtask: code + tests, fast gate, commit; then `/verify` |
| `/verify` | QA | Full gate + review + manual smoke (new features) |
| `/commit` | Implementation | Gated conventional commit (runs the canonical `ci.sh fast`) |
| `/release patch\|minor\|major` | Release | Version bump + changelog, then run `release.sh` locally |
| `/ship [IDs]\|"topic"` | Orchestration | plan â†’ implement â†’ verify â†’ merge â†’ release |
| `/pr [base]` | Review | Optional â€” open a PR (default merges locally) |
| `/resume` | Recovery | Continue interrupted work (reconstructs from the repo) |
| `/unsupervised on\|off` | Autonomy | No questions, autonomous defaults |
| `/workflow-decisions [setting]` | Config | View/change a workflow setting |
| `/workflow-update` | Maintenance | Update the workflow plugin |

## Configuration

Tunable settings (testing scope, branching model, deploy target, `ci-on-claude`, `release-runner`, GitHub integration, pause threshold) are recorded in [`decisions.md`](decisions.md). Change any with **`/workflow-decisions`**, which edits the live location and the record together.

## Specs

Specs live in `docs/specs/`: `backlog/` (raw drafts) â†’ `ready/` (planned) â†’ `completed/` (done).

## Quality Gates

| Gate | When | Who |
|------|------|-----|
| Auto-format | Every file edit | Hook |
| Fast gate (`ci.sh fast`) | Per subtask | `runner` (Haiku), locally |
| Full gate (`ci.sh full`) + smoke | Feature-done (`/verify`) | `runner` + `smoke-tester`, locally |
| Review | Critical diffs only | inline self-review, or the `reviewer` agent (best/high) |
| GitHub Actions CI | Human commits + releases only (Claude's carry `[skip ci]`) | GitHub Actions |
| Documentation | Inline during `/implement` (minimal) | main session |
